cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as word embeddings and downstream tasks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it evaluates the performance of pretrained embeddings on downstream tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word embeddings are often used in information retrieval tasks. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with language understanding and reasoning tasks. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural network models for word embeddings and downstream tasks.
